# Refactoring API Client & DevSecOps Validation

We successfully completed the migration of all `httpsCallable` and [fetch](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/layout/canvas/CanvasCatalogSidebar.tsx#37-137) calls within the `src/*` directory to the newly centralized [src/lib/api.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/lib/api.ts) client. Additionally, we've strengthened our deployment pipeline by rigorously passing DevSecOps validations across all three primary project parts (root, admin, functions).

## Changes Made
- Centralized the [callGateway](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/lib/api.ts#14-40) function within [src/lib/api.ts](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/lib/api.ts) making sure it properly carries all payloads while typing Responses with `Record<string, unknown>`.
- Refactored [OrganizationUsersCreate.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/OrganizationUsersCreate.tsx), [FormDetail.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/FormDetail.tsx), [FormLogin.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/FormLogin.tsx), [CanvasOnboarding.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/layout/canvas/CanvasOnboarding.tsx), [FormCreate.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/FormCreate.tsx), [FormOnboarding.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/FormOnboarding.tsx), and [FormList.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/FormList.tsx) to standardize API usage via [callGateway](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/lib/api.ts#14-40).
- Resolved generic Typescript `any` errors ensuring pure typings, e.g. mapping `Response.data` structures directly.
- Audited `root`, `admin`, and `functions` directories. They have been individually built, linted, and audited with **0 Vulnerabilities, 0 Errors, and 0 Warnings**.
- Elevated the Level 4 DevSecOps Tests in [pentest.mjs](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/scripts/pentest.mjs) (Directory Traversal checks: `/.env`, [/.env.local](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/.env.local), [/package.json](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/package.json)) from "NICE-TO-HAVE" to "MUST-HAVE".

## What Was Tested
- Typescript build steps (`npm run build`) in [app](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/layout/canvas/GenericPart.tsx#224-232), `admin`, and `functions`.
- Vulnerability analyses via `npm audit` across all three codebases environments simultaneously with no bypassing.
- The ISO 27001 automatic Pentest Script running against the active Next.js server locally confirming no Bypass leaks.
- `npm run cloud:validate` end-to-end to replicate pre-deployment safety steps.

## Validation Results
All tests and validations have **PASSED**. The `cloud:validate` pipeline confirms no vulnerabilities and 100% security baseline success.

```diff
-        const gatewayFn = httpsCallable(functions, "canvas");
-        const response = await gatewayFn({ actionId: "createCanvasSandbox", payload: { canvasType: "canvas", editPassword: autoPassword } });
-        const data = response.data as any;
+        const data = await callGateway<Record<string, unknown>>("canvas", { actionId: "createCanvasSandbox", payload: { canvasType: "canvas", editPassword: autoPassword } });
```
